# Goal Description
The user wants to generate an LLM summary for every document chunk using the Gemini API and store this summary in the PostgreSQL `chunk_profiles` table during the ingestion and profiling phase.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer
#### [MODIFY] [models.py](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/models.py)
- Add a new `summary` column of type `Text` (nullable=True) to the [ChunkProfile](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/models.py#46-100) SQLAlchemy model.

#### [MODIFY] [schemas.py](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/schemas.py)
- Add a `summary` field (type [str](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/service.py#80-82), default `""`) to the [ChunkProfileResult](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/schemas.py#50-82) Pydantic model.

### Service Layer
#### [NEW] [summary_generator.py](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/summary_generator.py)
- Create a new `SummaryGenerator` class.
- Initialize the Google GenAI client (using `gemini-2.0-flash` from settings).
- Implement a method `generate_summary_batch(texts: list[str]) -> list[str]` which takes a batch of chunk texts and uses the Gemini API to generate concise summaries concurrently.

#### [MODIFY] [service.py](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/service.py)
- Import and initialize the new `SummaryGenerator`.
- In [profile_document](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/service.py#50-145), add a call to `generate_summary_batch` alongside the other concurrent extraction tasks (`asyncio.gather`).
- Map the generated summaries to the [ChunkProfileResult](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/schemas.py#50-82) and update [_insert_postgres](file:///c:/HelioX/profiling/service.py#222-259) to save the `summary` value when inserting into the database.

### Integration / Viewer
#### [MODIFY] [run_pipeline.py](file:///c:/HelioX/run_pipeline.py)
- Update the mock profiling generation (Stage 0.5) to include a placeholder or mocked `summary` string so the script continues to function locally without breaking.

#### [MODIFY] [show_chunks_terminal.py](file:///c:/HelioX/show_chunks_terminal.py)
- Update the terminal viewer to query and display the new `summary` column straight from PostgreSQL instead of trying to reconstruct it from the raw ingestion text.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run the full existing pipeline `python run_test_pdf.py` and `python run_pipeline.py` to ensure the new summary step doesn't break the ingestion flow.
- The pipeline script runs the process locally, which will verify that the new DB column is written to correctly.

### Manual Verification
- After running the pipeline, execute `python show_chunks_terminal.py`. The terminal should successfully read from PostgreSQL and display the actual LLM-generated summaries next to their Chunk IDs.
